# Rename this file as harbour-defender.changes to include changelog
# entries in your RPM file.
#
# Add new changelog entries following the format below.
# Add newest entries to the top of the list.
# Separate entries from eachother with a blank line.

# * date Author's Name <author's email> version-release
# - Summary of changes
# * date Peter Leinchen <peterleinchen@t-online.de> vx.y.z

v0.8.9
- reorganized profile/permission (to the better?)
- fixed bug introduced with hotspot restart
- fixed re-calculation of cookies after manual deletion
- added sailjail enabling only for devices running SFOS >= 5
- for 10 III only: created a sub-division of lib whitelistings, merged only for this device
- introduced again error log visibility problem for browser in sailjail

 

v0.8.8
- with profile of 0.8.7 Defender starts on 10 III :), 
still bickering about some libs, so continuing testing whitelistings...
- added to restart hotspot if it was enabled before (connman, flush DNS)

 

v0.8.7
- fixed a typo in _updater.py regarding other user/dir names
- hopefully fixed lot of (all?) whitelists for 10 III
- moved all whitelistings from permission to profile (permission obsolete)

 

v0.8.6
- updated translations (all remorse popups)
- moved the ApppName translation tags to the correct section in desktop file

 

v0.8.5
- added support for all other user names (besides nemo and defaultuser) and even for different home directory
- disabled sailjail for all SFOS versions below 5.0
- added Spanish translation (courtesy of @carmenfdezb) - not yet completed
- included remorse (timer) popup strings in the translations

 

v0.8.4
- added translations for SV (courtesy of @eson) and DE (@peterleinchen)

 

v0.8.3
- huge debug session with @eson trying to find the culprit why Defender does not start in sailjail on 10 III, unsuccessful :( (missing libui_compat_layer.so)
- nevertheless updated permission and profile
- got rid of Documents.permission by moving errlog file to /var/log/defender_err.log
- added auomatic re-calculation of sources and cookies count
- added restart of connman after update (to flush DNS cache)

 

v0.8.2
- commented out func open_browser (forced a dependency on python-dbus)

 

v0.8.1
- finalized the sailjailed version
And that was more than a NIGHTMARE!
- added comment on cookies doc page regarding browser
- fixed exception on get_stats when browser is open

 

v0.8.0
- added supporting the sailjail restrictions, hopefully ;)
A nightmare, and definitely not worth the effort!



v0.7.4
- added the systemctl daemon-reload after installation (hopefully resolving the strang
e behaviour after first installation, see @eson)

 

v0.7.3
- changed the location of error log to ~/Documents/.defender_err.log (needed as sailfi
sh-browser is always sailfailed now)

  

v0.7.2
- fixed the AppSupport restart service to include the '@user', 
and hereby changed the location of /tmp dir and usr file(s)

  

v0.7.1
- added/fixed the file rights for cookies.sqlite DB and especially the -shm (and also -wal) additions by newer browser

  

Author: Peter Leinchen <peterleinchen@t-online.de>
